# Interacting with WebPage
1️⃣ What Does “Interacting with Webpage” Mean?
In selenium , Interation means:
    -> Finding HTML elements
    -> Clicking buttons
    -> Typing text
    -> Submitting forms
    -> Handling popups /iframes
    -> Extracting data

Opening a website using get() is just the beginning.
The real automation starts when we interact with elements.

2️⃣ Step 1 – Locate Elements
Before interacting, we must find the element.
Example HTML:
    <input type="text" name="passwd" id="passwd-id" />

Different Locator Strategies
    element = driver.find_element(By.ID, "passwd-id")
    element = driver.find_element(By.NAME, "passwd")
    element = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, "//input[@id='passwd-id']")

To Find Multiple Elements:
    elements = driver.find_elements(By.NAME, "passwd")

To Find Link by Text:
    element = driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, "Link Text")

⚠ Important Notes
1. If element not found → NoSuchElementException
2. If multiple elements match → first element is returned
3. Be careful while using XPath

3️⃣ After Locating an Element – What Can We Do?
✅ Type Text
    element.send_keys("some text")

✅ Press Keyboard Keys
    from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys
    element.send_keys(Keys.ARROW_DOWN)

✅ Clear Text Field
    element.clear()

✅ Click Element
    element.click()

4️⃣ Handling Iframes
Sometime elements are inside the iframe

Before interacting, we must switch to iframe:
    driver.switch_to.frame(iframe_element)

After finishing:
    driver.switch_to.default_content()
